  "prompt": "Why do five-star hotels not have water in washrooms, only tissues and dustbins?",
  "response": "Five-star hotels generally have water available in washrooms along with tissues and dustbins. The notion that they do not provide water in washrooms might be a misunderstanding or limited to a specific instance. High-end hotels prioritize guest comfort and hygiene, offering a range of amenities including water in various forms such as faucets, bidets, and sometimes high-tech automated toilets with built-in washing features.\n\nIf you have noticed the absence of water in washrooms at a particular five-star hotel, it could be due to local customs or a specific design choice rather than a general practice across all luxurious hotels. If you encounter this situation, you may address it with the hotel staff to understand their specific policies or request alternatives to meet your preferences.",
